Step-by-Step Explanation
1. Import Pandas Library
import pandas as pd
•	Imports the Pandas library. 
•	pd is the shortcut name for Pandas. 
________________________________________
2. Create Dataset
data={
    'Age':[22,45,35,60,27,32,49,55,36,47],
    'Income':[25000,50000,40000,75000,30000,35000,45000,60000,42000,55000]
}
•	Creates a dictionary containing: 
o	Age 
o	Income 
________________________________________
3. Convert into DataFrame
df=pd.DataFrame(data)
•	Converts the dictionary into a DataFrame (table format). 
Example:
Age	Income
22	25000
45	50000
35	40000
________________________________________
4. Create Age Groups
df['Age_group']=pd.cut(df['Age'],
                       bins=[0,30,50,100],
                       labels=['Young','Middle','Senior'])
Meaning:
pd.cut() divides age values into categories.
Bins:
•	0–30 → Young 
•	30–50 → Middle 
•	50–100 → Senior 
So:
•	Age 22 → Young 
•	Age 45 → Middle 
•	Age 60 → Senior 
________________________________________
